$interpreted: Local: It's the High Priest!
Devious: Children of the Snake God, is everyone okay?
Devious: I never would've thought they would use such cruel methods...tearing down your houses just to build the new Shrine. This is not the will of the Snake God.
Devious: I must apologize to you all...
Local: High Priest, please don't speak such nonsense. Of course we know you had nothing to do with this!
Humpty: High Priest, sir, wasn't this what you wanted me...
Devious: Although I can't rectify this, I will set up a temporary residence for you. Please, rest a while.
Local: Thank you, High Priest! Thank you so much, sir!
Jia-Shen: These wounds!? How'd this happen...!
Local: Granny Xica...! It was that rotten egg, Humpty...
Granny Xica: ...*cough*...*cough*...
Jia-Shen: It's all my fault. I shoulda never gone up and left ya'll.
Granny Xica: No, no...I was in the wrong. I shouldn't have spoken to you like that. I musta hurt your feelings pretty bad, no?
Jia-Shen: ...No, no. It was nothing. I forgot 'bout that long ago~
Jia-Shen: Meemaw, I best get to fixing you up. Ain't no time for chit chattin'.
Jia-Shen: Lord above! Why ain't this working!? It's all my fault, I ain't of no darned use at all!
Granny Xica: It's not your fault...I'm old, honey. I'm useless. I can't stay with you any longer...
Granny Xica: You best be going back to your hometown, now.
Jia-Shen: No! I don't wanna go back there!
Jia-Shen: I'm a grown fella and ain't nobody taken me in as family like Meemaw...without you, I ain't got nobody...
Granny Xica: Jia-Shen...*cough*...
Jia-Shen: Meemaw...!!!
Granny Xica: ...That's fine. If you don't want to go home, why don't you stay in the Desert Kingdom...
Granny Xica: Go to the western side, I've got some old friends there. They'll take care of you.
Jia-Shen: No! I ain't goin' nowhere. I'm gonna stay right by your side!
Granny Xica: Jia-Shen, listen to your Meemaw, won't you...?
Jia-Shen: Enough already! Why are you always so darn good to me!?
Jia-Shen: ...I'm just a useless stinker...this...
Granny Xica: ...Silly child...
Granny Xica: You'll understand when you're as old as Granny Xica.
Granny Xica: ...Even if you're of no use, you're the cutest of all my children...hehe...
Child: Brother Turtle.
Jia-Shen: Ya'll...
Child: Brother Turtle, what story are you gonna tell us today?
Jia-Shen: ......
Child: What about Granny Xica?
Child: Mama said Granny Xica went somewhere far, far away. Now there's no one to tell us stories. Is that true?
Jia-Shen: ......
Jia-Shen: Well ya'll just a weaving up a tall tale now, aren't ya? I'm a bobbing, weaving, scheming, dreaming, storytelling machine~
Jia-Shen: Children, chill-der-ran, gather round, gather round, don't be 'fraid of the tortoise clown~ Don't ya'll miss this chance to dance with chance! It's me, Jia-Shen...
